<proced xmlns:dc="http://www.purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.s1000d.org/S1000D_6/xml_schema_flat/proced.xsd">
  <title>DMC-S1000DBIKE-AAA-D05-20-00-00AA-000A-A_010-00_EN-US_1_1_regenerated_1_regenerated_2_regenerated_3_regenerated - Bicycle Maintenance Planning Document</title>
  <content>
    <section>
      <title>Overview</title>
      <paragraph>This document outlines the maintenance planning for a bicycle, detailing various tasks and their associated requirements.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>The document defines a series of maintenance tasks, each with specific prerequisites, resource needs, and inspection criteria.  Tasks vary in complexity and required skill level.</paragraph>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Maintenance Tasks</title>
      <task id="001">
        <worthinessLimit>Recommended</worthinessLimit>
        <applicabilityReference>app-MK1-9</applicabilityReference>
        <description>A routine inspection performed after each ride to identify immediate issues.</description>
        <prerequisites>None</prerequisites>
        <resources>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Operator</role>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.1</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
        </resources>
        <inspectionCriteria>Visual check for damage or wear.</inspectionCriteria>
        <trigger>After each ride.</trigger>
      </task>
      <task id="002">
        <worthinessLimit>Recommended</worthinessLimit>
        <applicabilityReference>app-MK1-9</applicabilityReference>
        <description>Checking and adjusting tire pressure.</description>
        <prerequisites>None</prerequisites>
        <resources>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Operator</role>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.1</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
          <equipment>
            <item>Tire pressure gauge</item>
            <item>pump</item>
          </equipment>
        </resources>
        <inspectionCriteria>Tire pressure within recommended range.</inspectionCriteria>
        <trigger>Weekly or before each longer ride.</trigger>
      </task>
      <task id="003">
        <worthinessLimit>Recommended</worthinessLimit>
        <applicabilityReference>app-MK1-9</applicabilityReference>
        <description>Inspecting brake pads, cables, and levers for wear or damage.</description>
        <prerequisites>None</prerequisites>
        <resources>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Operator</role>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.2</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
        </resources>
        <inspectionCriteria>Proper brake function and pad thickness.</inspectionCriteria>
        <trigger>Weekly or before each ride.</trigger>
      </task>
      <task id="004">
        <worthinessLimit>Recommended</worthinessLimit>
        <applicabilityReference>app-MK1-9</applicabilityReference>
        <description>Applying lubricant to the chain for smooth operation.</description>
        <prerequisites>None</prerequisites>
        <resources>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Operator</role>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.1</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
          <equipment>
            <item>Lubricant</item>
            <item>rag</item>
          </equipment>
        </resources>
        <inspectionCriteria>Chain visibly lubricated.</inspectionCriteria>
        <trigger>As needed, based on riding conditions.</trigger>
      </task>
      <task id="005">
        <worthinessLimit>Recommended</worthinessLimit>
        <applicabilityReference>app-MK1-9</applicabilityReference>
        <description>Cleaning the hub bearings.</description>
        <prerequisites>Rear wheel removed (referenced DM Code: S1000DBIKE, system DA0, sub-system 2)</prerequisites>
        <resources>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Supervisor</role>
            <skillLevel>sk03</skillLevel>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.8</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
          <personnel>
            <quantity>1</quantity>
            <role>Operator</role>
            <estimatedTime unit="hours">0.3</estimatedTime>
          </personnel>
          <equipment>
            <item>Specialist toolset</item>
          </equipment>
          <supplies>
            <item>Degreasing agent</item>
            <item>general grease</item>
          </supplies>
        </resources>
        <inspectionCriteria>Smooth bearing rotation.</inspectionCriteria>
        <trigger>Every 6 months or after excessive exposure to water/dirt.</trigger>
        <externalRequirement>Referenced external publication: D6-1234, "My Publication", January 2007, Rev 1.</externalRequirement>
      </task>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Key Considerations</title>
      <paragraph>Tasks require varying levels of skill, from basic operator tasks to those requiring a qualified supervisor/mechanic.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>Some tasks reference external documents or DM codes for more detailed information.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>Each task has a defined trigger for when it should be performed.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>The &lt;code/&gt; (app-MK1-9) likely refers to a higher-level document defining the scope and context of this maintenance plan.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>Tasks like Hub Bearing Cleaning have defined thresholds (e.g., 6 months) and limits for inspection.</paragraph>
    </section>
  </content>
